data.text:
How to use ICICI Silapathar IFSC code in online fund transfer?

ICICI Silapathar IFSC code is an 11 digit code used in online fund transfers. This IFSC code contains 4 Characters that represent ICICI Bank, 5th character is reserved for future use and the last 6 characters represent the Silapathar branch code. ICICI Bank has many branches all over the country and physical cheques cannot be transferred anywhere across the country to transfer funds hence internet banking is preferred. The IFSC code ICIC0005293 is used to identify the Industrial Credit And Investment Corporation Of India Silapathar participating in online transactions via RTGS, IMPS and NEFT systems.
